The paper proposes a privacy-preserving algorithm for solving Distributed Constraint Optimization Problems (DCOPs) that is immune to coalitions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) since DCOPs are a common problem in multi-agent systems, Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) since the paper focuses on privacy and security, Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) since the paper deals with distributed algorithms, Machine Learning (cs.LG) since the paper proposes a new algorithm, and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) since the paper deals with multi-agent systems.
